Eggdrop Build Guide
===================

Detailed build instructions and troubleshooting. For the quick-start
version, see the INSTALL file.


Requirements
------------

  - Meson >= 0.63
  - Ninja
  - C compiler with C23 support (GCC 11+, Clang 13+)
  - Tcl >= 8.6 (optional, for Tcl scripting)
  - Python >= 3.8 (optional, for Python scripting)

TLS is provided by the bundled opssl library — no external OpenSSL or
wolfSSL installation needed. IPv6 is always compiled in.

At least one of Tcl or Python should be present for scripting support.
Neither is required for the bot to connect and manage channels.


Standard build
--------------

    meson setup builddir
    ninja -C builddir
    ninja -C builddir install

Common options:

    -Dtcl=disabled          Build without Tcl
    -Dpython=auto           Enable Python if found
    -Dtls=disabled          Disable TLS (not recommended)
    -Dmodule-python=false   Skip python.mod
    -Dprefix=$HOME/eggdrop  Custom install path
    -Degg-debug=true        ASAN + UBSAN debug build
    -Dbuildtype=debug       Debug symbols for crash analysis


Advanced options
----------------

List all options:

    meson configure builddir

Modify after setup:

    meson configure builddir -Doption=value


Platform notes
--------------

Linux:

  I/O backend auto-detected: io_uring (5.1+), epoll, or select.
  No additional configuration needed.

macOS:

  Uses kqueue for event-driven I/O. TLS is bundled (opssl).

  If Meson cannot find Tcl:

      brew install tcl-tk
      export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=$(brew --prefix tcl-tk)/lib/pkgconfig

FreeBSD / OpenBSD / NetBSD:

  Uses kqueue. Install: pkg install meson ninja tcl

Windows (MSYS2 / MinGW-w64):

  Use the UCRT64 shell. Winsock2 and MsWSock (for IOCP) ship with the
  Windows SDK and are linked automatically.

Windows (MSVC):

  Use an x64 Native Tools Command Prompt. Point PKG_CONFIG_PATH at
  vcpkg output. Add --vsenv to meson setup.

Cygwin:

  POSIX emulation layer — uses select() as I/O backend. Does not
  expose Win32 IOCP APIs.

Cross-compilation:

  Create a Meson cross-file:

      [binaries]
      c = 'arm-linux-gnueabihf-gcc'
      ar = 'arm-linux-gnueabihf-ar'

  Then: meson setup builddir --cross-file=cross.ini


Tcl detection
-------------

If Meson cannot find Tcl automatically, specify paths:

    meson setup builddir \
      -Dtcl_include_path=/path/to/tcl/include \
      -Dtcl_lib_path=/path/to/tcl/lib

To compile Tcl from source:

    tar -zxf tcl<VERSION>-src.tar.gz
    cd tcl<VERSION>/unix
    ./configure --prefix=$HOME/tcl
    make && make install
    export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$HOME/tcl/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH


FAQ
---

Q: I get build warnings — is that a problem?

  Warnings do not prevent a successful build. The codebase builds
  with zero warnings on GCC 15. If you see warnings on a different
  compiler, they are likely harmless. Errors (not warnings) cause
  build failure.

Q: Compiler does not support C23 features.

  GCC 11+ or Clang 13+ is required. Update your compiler.

Q: How do I enable/disable specific modules?

    meson setup builddir -Dmodule-compress=false
    meson configure builddir | grep module-

Q: "Tcl not found" error.

  Install Tcl dev headers (tcl-dev, tcl-devel, or tcl-tk depending
  on distro), or build with -Dtcl=disabled to skip Tcl entirely.

Q: "Meson" or "Ninja" not found.

  Install them: apt install meson ninja-build (Debian/Ubuntu),
  dnf install meson ninja-build (Fedora), brew install meson ninja
  (macOS), pkg install meson ninja (FreeBSD).

Q: Permission denied on install.

  Use sudo ninja -C builddir install, or set a user-writable prefix:
  meson setup builddir --prefix=$HOME/eggdrop


